# Armor and Protection

How you protect yourself shapes everything about how you fight. Armor isn't just about reducing damage—it's a fundamental tactical choice that affects your mobility, your spellcasting, your Momentum generation, and your entire approach to combat.

The heavily armored paladin standing immovable on the front line and the unarmored monk flowing around attacks represent opposite ends of the protection spectrum. Both work mechanically. Neither is universally better. The question isn't "which armor is best" but "which armor suits how I want to play."

